text: Mohamad bin Aziz (29 July 1940 â€“ 24 December 2020) was a Malaysian politician. He was a member of the Parliament of Malaysia for the Sri Gading constituency in the state of Johor from 1999 to 2013. He was a member of the United Malays National Organisation (UMNO) party. Percentage figures are calculated based on total turnout. Includes results from the 2004 election. Results from earlier elections are not available. Aziz was born in Batu Pahat, Johor. Aziz died on 24 December 2020 at the age of 80. ==References== Category:1940 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Malaysian politicians Category:People from Johor
